President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed October 16 through October 22, 2022, as National Character Counts Week. During this week, Americans are encouraged to reflect on and engage in efforts that embody the highest standards of character, including integrity, courage, empathy, decency, and respect. The proclamation highlights the importance of simple acts of kindness and selflessness, which showcase the best of America's character. It also emphasizes the role of character in various sectors, such as education, healthcare, and public service. President Biden reaffirms his commitment to championing policies that reflect the values our nation stands for, including unity, combating hate and racism, ending hunger, and addressing everyday issues. The proclamation concludes with a call for all Americans to honor and express the best attributes of their character, extend fellowship to their neighbors, and unite in service to their communities.